<p>In light of Texas A&amp;M&#8217;s decision to tell a philosophy professor to <a href="https://dailynous.com/2026/01/06/texas-am-bans-plato/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">remove readings by Plato from his course</a>, one enterprising philosopher has come up with a way for people to voice their support for academic freedom.<span id="more-56156"></span></p>
<p>It&#8217;s the &#8220;<a href="https://www.zazzle.com/legalize_plato_shirt-256698641826369214" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Legalize Plato</a>&#8221; t-shirt.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-56157 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-1.png" alt="t-shirt model wearing shirt that says &quot;legalize plato&quot;" width="600" height="383" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-1.png 1066w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-1-300x192.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-1-1024x654.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-1-768x491.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-1-400x256.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p>Designed by UC San Diego philosophy professor <a href="https://philosophy.ucsd.edu/people/faculty-sites/sbazargan.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Saba Bazargan</a>, the &#8220;Legalize Plato&#8221; shirt is available for purchase in a variety of colors and fits <strong><a href="https://www.zazzle.com/legalize_plato_shirt-256698641826369214" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a></strong>.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.zazzle.com/legalize_plato_shirt-256698641826369214"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-56158 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-2.png" alt="" width="600" height="470" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-2.png 1044w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-2-300x235.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-2-1024x802.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-2-768x602.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/legalize-plato-shirt-2-400x313.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a></p>
<p>(Yes, the style is an intentional homage to the &#8220;Legalize LA&#8221; shirt.)</p>
<p>(No, there&#8217;s no need to point out in the comments that Texas A&amp;M did not or could not technically make Plato <em>illegal</em>. Please.)</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2026/01/08/legalize-plato-the-shirt/">Legalize Plato: The Shirt</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>